POD1000000013_S0000031	and I was dealt with unfairly and I wanted to be a lawyer because I was going to help people that were treated unfairly.
POD1000000013_S0000032	So that's what made me want to be a lawyer really.
POD1000000013_S0000033	Yeah, okay.
POD1000000013_S0000034	And after university, I know you became a solicitor, but was that straight away?
POD1000000013_S0000035	Yes, yes, I didn't. I know nowadays there's a gap here.
POD1000000013_S0000036	But yes, I went to the Institute of Legal Studies and practiced as a solicitor in private practice and then in the public sector.
POD1000000013_S0000037	mostly litigation, but started to focus on human rights and data protection, freedom of information when I was in the public sector.
POD1000000013_S0000038	So when did you join the Information Commissioner's office?
POD1000000013_S0000039	2003.
POD1000000013_S0000040	Okay, and what did you do before then?
POD1000000013_S0000041	Before then I worked for the housing authority.
POD1000000013_S0000042	I worked for 17 years in the legal department of the Housing Authority dealing with intractable problems such as anti-social behaviour, homelessness, fractured communities who had to be housed near to each other.
POD1000000013_S0000043	Yeah.
POD1000000013_S0000044	So issues such as peace walls.
