POD1000000026_S0000115	We had been working on Bourbon for a while, eight, nine months or something by that time.
POD1000000026_S0000116	And we were meeting one of our early investors.
POD1000000026_S0000117	And he was like, so what are you building? What's up? Like what's new?
POD1000000026_S0000118	And we're like, well, you know, we have these features and it does this thing and it does this thing.
POD1000000026_S0000119	And his face was just blank.
POD1000000026_S0000120	Like he's just looking at us like, what are you talking about? I don't understand what you're trying to build.
POD1000000026_S0000121	And we were so sad after that meeting because it was so clear to us that we couldn't explain what we were working on.
POD1000000026_S0000122	So we went back to the office, we sat in front of a whiteboard and we said, okay, we have to focus this thing.
POD1000000026_S0000123	It's trying to do too much all at once.
POD1000000026_S0000124	So we stripped everything away that day.
POD1000000026_S0000125	and we focused just on the components that would effectively become Instagram.
POD1000000026_S0000126	and maybe in the course of a week or two, made the first version of Instagram.
POD1000000026_S0000127	I spent far more time with Kevin than any other human being for that first year of Instagram, easily, right? Like we were in there every single day.
POD1000000026_S0000128	12, 13, 14 hours, sometimes overnight.
POD1000000026_S0000129	you know, Mike would be brushing his teeth in the employee bathroom, you know, at 4am just because like we had been there all night.
POD1000000026_S0000130	We got to launch day, we launched it to the world.
POD1000000026_S0000131	October 6, 2010. I know that date and the date of my daughter's birth. Those are the two dates I will never forget, right?
POD1000000026_S0000132	People liked it. People started using it.
POD1000000026_S0000133	And I was taken aback because I mean, I had worked at a company before that struggled to get 10,000 people to use it over a year.
POD1000000026_S0000134	And we got to 25,000 that first day.
POD1000000026_S0000135	And I remember turning to Mike and I said, I think we've created something.
POD1000000026_S0000136	I'm usually the pessimist and Mike is usually, I'm not sure, optimist, but you're pragmatist, right?
POD1000000026_S0000137	But like I had this moment of clarity that there was something special because I had never seen people react this way.
POD1000000026_S0000138	And Mike just looked at me like, I don't know, maybe not. Maybe this is all going to come crashing down.
POD1000000026_S0000139	The one little dinky server that we had was just like metaphorically and perhaps physically melting by all the traffic that was coming at it.
POD1000000026_S0000140	I really felt like we had squandered this opportunity.
POD1000000026_S0000141	And I was like, we should probably add another server.
POD1000000026_S0000142	And Kevin was like, no, we don't need another server.
POD1000000026_S0000143	And in retrospect, I think it was like, we didn't know if this thing was going to take off and it was expensive to add another server. Like, did we really need it?
POD1000000026_S0000144	And I was like, no, I think we do.
POD1000000026_S0000145	And then like later he's like, oh man, sorry, like I was a little heated
POD1000000026_S0000146	You know, we had been up for 36 hours at that point, you know, kind of fighting off sleep and also excited.
POD1000000026_S0000148	both the best and worst days of our lives.
POD1000000026_S0000149	like you know the thing was working but also was crashing.
POD1000000026_S0000150	I think that was like the only time we've ever raised our voices with each other.
POD1000000026_S0000151	It was brief. It was like a probably 30 second interaction.
POD1000000026_S0000152	I approve this message.
POD1000000026_S0000154	Which is true, like that was the one time that it was heated and it was just the heat of the moment.
POD1000000026_S0000155	I'm actually going to take it way back at our first disagreement, which actually I haven't thought about in many years.
POD1000000026_S0000156	two or three weeks into working together. I remember coming in one day and saying,
