POD1000000026_S0000164	if I had to like abstract it and what I learned about working with Kevin over the years it was I don't think you're ever a person that will just agree to something because it will make somebody else happy.
POD1000000026_S0000165	But you also make sure that in disagreeing you're also not being a jerk and making them feel bad about feeling differently. You're like,
POD1000000026_S0000166	Now I've thought about this and here's what I want to do for it.
POD1000000026_S0000167	Is there like a reason why you really feel differently and then we can have the conversation?
POD1000000026_S0000168	That sort of like detoxified ability to disagree is really important.
POD1000000026_S0000169	I get annoyed really easily.
POD1000000026_S0000170	But the interesting thing is Mike doesn't annoy me. Like he really doesn't.
POD1000000026_S0000171	Like, I really don't get annoyed with Mike because he has character and integrity.
POD1000000026_S0000172	Those are the two things I care about.
