POD1000000026_S0000175	Mike has never made except for that one time on the server issue. Mike has never made me angry.
POD1000000026_S0000176	I don't think we ever actually had titles for the longest time.
POD1000000026_S0000177	I guess once we started doing public events and we had to talk about what our titles were
POD1000000026_S0000178	There was a time where we were like, okay, you're CTO, I'm CEO. We kind of like divided it that way.
POD1000000026_S0000179	but you always say co-founder first. That's the title.
POD1000000026_S0000180	When I thought about my identity and what we were doing in the company, I was like, co-founder, maybe technical co-founder if you wanted to put an adjective in front of it.
POD1000000026_S0000181	required technical co-founders.
POD1000000026_S0000184	But I do also think the SpeakStar personality and our relationship, it is really important for any company to ultimately have one final decision maker.
POD1000000026_S0000185	I've seen so many companies not have one and it become a mess. Sometimes there's a tie break needed or sometimes like a call needs to get made.
POD1000000026_S0000186	you really need to find somebody who's willing to like make that call and you all have to be ready to like make that person successful in that role or else it's just not gonna work.
POD1000000026_S0000187	We had a bunch of people that really wanted Instagram inside of their company.
POD1000000026_S0000188	But we were having so much fun doing our own thing that we just didn't want to be part of any other company.
POD1000000026_S0000189	We didn't want to be a wing of a building. We wanted to be the building.
