POD1000000030_S0000028	It is, and I think it should be, but there have to be some restrictions to how far you go.
POD1000000030_S0000029	We don't want people to be tempted to amputate their lower legs so they can go from a 215 marathoner to a 205 marathoner.
POD1000000030_S0000030	Our legs aren't built just for running. They're built for climbing and swimming and jumping and all kinds of activities.
POD1000000030_S0000031	So if you tune the leg to be tuned just for running, they'll be great at running but not good at other things
POD1000000030_S0000032	And that's where you could go if you didn't have rules established.
