YOU1000000021_S0000000	Released by Square Enix in 2007 on the PlayStation Portable, director Hajime Tabata and writer Kazushika Nojima worked together to create a prequel to Final Fantasy VII for its 10th anniversary.
YOU1000000021_S0000001	The game sets up the world and role of many characters from the main game, and focuses on developing several figures such as Zack, Aerith, Sephiroth, and key members of Shinra.
YOU1000000021_S0000002	The story and gameplay are done solely from the perspective of Zack, and features full voice acting. For combat, random encounters are utilized while actual combat is similar to the Kingdom Hearts menu-based real-time system.
YOU1000000021_S0000003	Mechanics such as the equipment and materials system have been majorly overhauled and removed to reduce player macro-management, and instead contribute to the main battle modifier, the digital mindwave.
YOU1000000021_S0000004	The DMW is a continuously spinning slot machine system that confers various bonuses, effects, and attacks based on the results, including how Zack levels up.
YOU1000000021_S0000005	The campaign is progressed through missions the player can select at their own pace, or complete sidequests instead, traveling instantly to many fully 3D areas and dungeons with no need for an overworld map.
YOU1000000021_S0000006	The story only gets larger from here, so let's cut it down to size with a recapitation.
YOU1000000021_S0000007	The game begins with Zack Fair, Soldier 2nd Class of the group called Soldier, a private military army owned by the Shinra Electric Power Company in the city of Midgar.
YOU1000000021_S0000008	He completes a training exercise under the mentorship of his friend and commander, Angeal, a first class soldier.
YOU1000000021_S0000009	Zack has tremendous skills and talent, but is unfortunately a little overconfident and reckless at times, as pointed out by his fellow soldier, another first class named Sephiroth.
YOU1000000021_S0000010	Zack idolizes Sephiroth as a hero and aspires to one day be at his level, but he's not ready yet, despite this Sephiroth only being part of the training simulation.
YOU1000000021_S0000011	and Jill helps him out, reminding him to temper his aspirations with passionate dreams and steadfast honor.
YOU1000000021_S0000012	Zack hears from a fellow soldier of the mass desertion of troops in Soldier, and he's soon called in to speak with the director of Soldier, a man named Lanzard.
YOU1000000021_S0000013	He's briefed about soldier First Class Genesis, who went missing during a mission in Wutai, an independent country to the west against whom Shinra Company is personally leveraging its military might.
