YOU1000000124_S0000027	So we got over this problem that until then neural networks just had hand-designed features, they waited those features to make a decision, and then they made a decision.
YOU1000000124_S0000028	They didn't learn their own features. With backpropagation we could learn lesser features, and there's a lot of hype about how this was going to solve everything. And that's what I believed.
YOU1000000124_S0000029	That is, I believed in the 80s that what's happening today was going to happen then, and it didn't.
YOU1000000124_S0000031	In the 1990s
YOU1000000124_S0000033	People showed there were other machine learning algorithms that worked better than backpropagation on modest-sized problems. Things called support-vector machines.
YOU1000000124_S0000034	They had fancier math, and they worked a little bit better on what we now think of as very small problems, things with a few thousand training examples.
YOU1000000124_S0000036	So your lab will wipe that again.
