YOU1000000124_S0000043	So, the old way to make a computer do what you wanted was to write a program.
YOU1000000124_S0000044	where you figured out how you would do it yourself, and then you explain to the computer in exquisite detail how to do what you would have done yourself, but a whole lot faster.
YOU1000000124_S0000046	So if I wanted to sort a list, for example, I would figure out, well, I'm not a computer scientist, which we'll quickly realize.
YOU1000000124_S0000047	I would figure out, well, I could go down the list and find the biggest thing and then put that at the top. And then I could go down the list again and find the next biggest thing and put that underneath those things.
YOU1000000124_S0000048	It's not a good algorithm, but I might decide to do it like that. And then I could tell the computer to do that, and then the computer would sort of list faster than I could.
YOU1000000124_S0000050	The new way to do it is to, you first tell the computer to pretend to be a neural network.
YOU1000000124_S0000052	And then you just show it examples. So you've shown an example of an unsorted list and a sorted list. And you show lots of examples, and you say, I want you to take these things and produce those things.
