YOU1000000175_S0000019	new residents starting, new faculty starting around July, then isn't that a more dangerous time to be in hospital? And there have been 300 studies looking into this.
YOU1000000175_S0000020	And it turns out that it depends on what kind of hospital it is, who you're being looked after, like how experienced they are, but also what kind of illness you are and how seriously sick you are.
YOU1000000175_S0000021	The take home from this is that if you're sick in July, you still need to go to a hospital and by and large, you're in good hands.
